project-inspiration: Are passphrases really that much harder to guess than passwords?  Natural language models can help evaluate them.  Character entropy isn't always a good measure of strength since dictionary words are easy to guess and could have high character entropy.
project-lessons-learned: I learned more about GUI development and schema design.

team.participant-bubble: I cleaned the data, put it into a database, conceived of a model, and developed a Python interface.
